name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank1Convo4_403
text_en: I escaped a personal hell only to wind up in a system where the universe was overtaken by a madman bent on total domination.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank1Convo4_404
text_en: The only place I've ever really known as home is a derelict ship trapped like a cork in a rift in dimensions, inhabited by ghosts and terrible memories.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank1Convo4_405
text_en: I was trapped for untold centuries in an infinitely looping dimension where I was subject to torture and murder at the hands of a child despot.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank1Convo4_406
text_en: I had to fight, largely on my own, to free the Origin System's brainwashed innocents to try to rise up and fight the two lunatics in charge of it.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank1Convo4_407
text_en: That was the first place I met the Indifference. It wouldn't be the last. But that was where the Man in the Wall took *everything* from me.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank1Convo4_408
text_en: Who, by the way, was a creation of my own memories when the Void reached into my mind and pulled out fragments of a storybook.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank1Convo4_409
text_en: One of whom is the brother of the thing that saved my life. Ultimately... we won. But I still remember the terror... the fear.

text_en: I don't really buy into that kind of "winner take all" philosophy, personally. There has to be more to life.

text_en: Things have just gotten more complicated, but the base problems are all the same. People are still people.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank3Convo2_948
text_en: In short, the Orokin decided they were gods. They're enhanced humans who figured out how to live forever. Sentients were created by the Orokin to terraform another solar system, but then turned around and waged war on the Orokin Empire.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank3Convo2_949
text_en: The Orokin Empire were - are? - responsible for a lot of of the mess we're dealing with now. Either directly or indirectly.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank3Convo2_950
text_en: Earth and the rest of the system was becoming uninhabitable. And they wanted to ensure the survival of the human race. So they decided to terraform a new solar system and it's main planet, Tau.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank3Convo2_951
text_en: In order to do that, they created a synthetic race. The Sentients. And then the Sentients came back and waged war on the Orokin Empire about it.

text_en: You would make one *hell* of a Corpus commander. They'd love you. You'd have no problem crushing the Solari under your boot and collecting their limbs for debts.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2167
text_en: So you think that if you have a genuine connection to someone... you're... in debt to them. Why?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2168
text_en: n i'm not letting it happen 2 me again. never. FKING. AGAIN. read me?!

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2169
text_en: how many ppl have you almost died 4? HAVE died 4? u get 2 come back. every time i let somebody in, i get in2 serious shit

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2170
text_en: bc i'm not stupid either!! look around! its just the way the world works. look at u, risking ur life for us losers

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2171
text_en: doesn't mean i like it, u ABSOLUTE wanker. i don't want the world 2 work this way! don't want 2 see ppl get crushed up in the gears of it

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2172
text_en: but ppl like me learn real fast that either u play the game or u. get. played. n i'm not here 2 get played by anybody. not even u

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2173
text_en: n i'm not gonna let myself get played by anybody ever again. NEVER. FKING. AGAIN. read me?! not even by u. especially not by u

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2174
text_en: Too afraid to admit that he might actually have a *genuine connection* with someone because that means making himself *vulnerable.*

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2175
text_en: I don't need to tell you a story to get you to hate me. I can get it done in two words.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2176
text_en: I don't play games like this. I don't need this kind of shit in my life. I'm out. [End.]

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2177
text_en: You want to hate me? You want to drive me away? All right. I'll give you a reason to hate me.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2178
text_en: lets hear it

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2179
text_en: nah. no u don't. u don't get 2 just walk away from this. u do? u walk away permanently, read me? this stops. this cute little texty bullshit we got goin' on STOPS

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2180
text_en: so either give me what i want or we done

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2181
text_en: Grow. Up.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2182
text_en: Then we're done.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2183
text_en: Whatever. You win. Let's go.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2184
text_en: You want the story of the absolute worst thing I've ever done in my life? The most reprehensible and unforgivable thing?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2185
text_en: Here it is.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2186
text_en: And if that wasn't some part of my mind punishing me, over and over again, for what I'd done?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2187
text_en: The thing that keeps me up at night, makes me stare at the ceiling and wonder if I didn't deserve all those executions in Duviri?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2188
text_en: I killed my parents.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2189
text_en: I locked my parents up in a makeshift prison... and waited for them to die.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2190
text_en: I stood by and watched as my friends killed my parents.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2191
text_en: [End.]

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2192
text_en: When I was onboard the Zariman, and the Indifference arrived, it decided it wanted to perform a little experiment.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2193
text_en: Could you really do the unthinkable? Make *parents* want to murder their own *children?*

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2194
text_en: And... what would happen if you then armed the children with Void powers...?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2195
text_en: Would the children kill their own parents in self defense? Or would they let nature take its course? Would they rather rely on others to do the deed?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2196
text_en: Or would they just... let their parents rip them to pieces like the blood-crazed creatures they'd been reduced to?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2197
text_en: And I spared some of my friends that fate that day in exchange. I don't know if I regret my choice or not. Sometimes I think I do.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2198
text_en: But then I remember the looks on the faces of those who chose to do the deed themselves and I think... no. There's a difference between cowardly and smart.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2199
text_en: Sometimes I wonder if my choice was the cowardly one - letting my friends do the deed for me.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2200
text_en: I don't know if I regret not making it quick for them or not. Sometimes I do. Sometimes I think... no. I would have always given them that chance to snap out of it.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2201
text_en: But then I realize that a quick death for them would've been a mercy for me. Watching them slowly die... as they screamed and foamed at the mouth and wore their limbs to bloody stumps in their desperate attempt to kill me...?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2202
text_en: Sometimes I wonder if I was the coward. For locking them up and hoping they'd snap out of it. For watching themselves claw their hands to bone trying to escape their cage.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2203
text_en: But then I remember all the kids who couldn't do it, and left their parents moldering in cages for however long it was until they got rescued. Watching them tear themselves to pieces like feral, mad animals. I don't know which is worse.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2204
text_en: Sometimes I wonder what kind of monster a person has to be to kill their own parents. To look at their faces, twisted in anger and monstrous hunger and to end their lives.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2205
text_en: I don't know if I regret killing them quickly. And not trying to save them like other people did. Or... letting someone else do the deed for me. Sometimes I think I do.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2206
text_en: This is what it took from me that day. And that is what I will fight to keep alive. One idiot at a time, if I have to.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2207
text_en: Because this connection? This is what the Indifference is trying to murder from the world.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2208
text_en: That's why I dedicate my life to doing exactly what you're afraid to do, Quincy. I let people in, when you shut people out.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2209
text_en: But there is one where I did. Two, if you want to be exact. And in those two worlds... we can still make a difference for people. We can still help them.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2210
text_en: But that's the thing about life, isn't it? You make choices. And you're always left wondering if you made the right ones. I do know this much - there's no world in which they survived the Indifference.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2211
text_en: Tah-dah.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2212
text_en: So. Do you hate me yet?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyRank5Convo1_2213
text_en: How was that? Or should I come kick you in the balls to top it off?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyRank5Convo1_2214
text_en: ...we r not done here

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyDay2_2223
text_en: u failed

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyDay2_2224
text_en: Ok.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyDay2_2225
text_en: At what?

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/Choice_QuincyDay2_2226
text_en: Oh good, we're still going.

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyDay2_2227
text_en: shove it

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyDay2_2228
text_en: u were supposed 2 make me hate u

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyDay2_2229
text_en: that was the whole fkin POINT of this FKING EXERCISE N U FAILED

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyDay2_2230
text_en: n now - FK. FK...

text_en: told u it wasn't gonna be fun when i came 2 tell u the story of how i joined the hex

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyDay2_2232
text_en: but now it's gonna happen. b/c now it's my turn 2 tell u the story that'll make u hate me

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyDay2_2233
text_en: now it's my turn 2 tell u the story that'll make u hate me

name: /Lotus/Language/1999Texting/QuincyRomance/TxtQuincy_QuincyDay2_2234
text_en: bc somebody's gotta do this job RIGHT n if it's not gonna be u? it's gonna come down 2 me. like it always fkin' does

text_en: All right. I'm listening.

text_en: You don't need to do this, Quincy.

text_en: I'm walking away. I'm not playing this game. [End.]

text_en: yeah. i do. n once u listen 2 what i've got 2 say, maybe u'll FINALLY understand y

text_en: maybe once u hear what i've got 2 say, maybe u'll FINALLY understand
